         <div xml:id="alalal-d99301"><!-- l2d36dt -->
            <head xml:id="alalal-d99301-Hd1e99">Divisio Textus</head>
            <p xml:id="alalal-d99301-d1e101">
               <cb ed="#Bc" n="b"/>
               <lb ed="#Bc" n="13"/>DIVISIO TEXTUS.
</p>
            <p xml:id="alalal-d99301-d1e108">
               <lb ed="#Bc" n="14"/>
               <quote xml:id="alalal-d99301-Qd1e112"> Sciendum est tamen quaedam sie
<lb ed="#Bc" n="15"/>esse peccata, etc. </quote>
               <lb ed="#Bc" n="16"/>Adhuc autem divisio inducitur sub 
opi<lb break="no" ed="#Bc" n="17"/>nione prehabiti per modum 
disputatio<lb break="no" ed="#Bc" n="18"/>nis. Queritur enim ab ista opinione,
<lb ed="#Bc" n="19"/>Utrum peccatum in quantum poena est,
<lb ed="#Bc" n="20"/>a Deo sit, vel actus peccati sit a Deo ? et,
<lb ed="#Bc" n="21"/>Si per modum pene a Deo sit? et,
<lb ed="#Bc" n="22"/>Utram omne peccatum sit poena in
<lb ed="#Bc" n="23"/>quantum peccatum est ?
</p>
            <p xml:id="alalal-d99301-d1e135">
               <lb ed="#Bc" n="24"/>Hec autem distinctio dividitur in duas
<lb ed="#Bc" n="25"/>partes : in quarum prima ostendit 
quali<lb break="no" ed="#Bc" n="26"/>ter peccatum accipit rationem pene. In
<lb ed="#Bc" n="27"/>secunda autem ponit epilogum istius
<lb ed="#Bc" n="28"/>opinionis, ibi, K, <quote xml:id="alalal-d99301-Qd1e148"> Satés diligenter,
<lb ed="#Bc" n="29"/>etc. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="alalal-d99301-d1e154">
               <lb ed="#Bc" n="30"/>Prior adhue subdividitur in duas : in
<cb ed="#Bc" n="c"/>
               <lb ed="#Bc" n="31"/>quarum prima ostendit esse peccatum
<lb ed="#Bc" n="32"/>penam. In secunda autem dissolvit
<lb ed="#Bc" n="33"/>quamdam contrarietatem quae videtur
<lb ed="#Bc" n="34"/>esse inter Augustinum et Hieronymum,
<lb ed="#Bc" n="35"/>ibi, H, <quote xml:id="alalal-d99301-Qd1e171"> Illud autem diligenter, etc. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="alalal-d99301-d1e175">
               <lb ed="#Bc" n="36"/>In prima facit quatuor. Primo, probat
<lb ed="#Bc" n="37"/>omne peccatum poenam esse. In secundo
<lb ed="#Bc" n="38"/>capitulo querit, Utrum in quantum 
pec<lb break="no" ed="#Bc" n="39"/>catum,vel non ? et determinat, quod non,
<lb ed="#Bc" n="40"/>ibi, B, <quote xml:id="alalal-d99301-Qd1e188"> Bt ideo merito.queritur, etc. </quote>
               <lb ed="#Bc" n="41"/>In tertio capitulo querit, Utrum unum
<lb ed="#Bc" n="42"/>peccatum sit poena alterius? ibi, C, <quote xml:id="alalal-d99301-Qd1e194"> #¢
<lb ed="#Bc" n="43"/>leet ex hoc sensu, etc. </quote> In quarto, 
os<lb break="no" ed="#Bc" n="44"/>tendit hoc specialiter in quibusdam 
pec<lb break="no" ed="#Bc" n="45"/>catis, quod sunt poena: et hoc dupliciter :
<lb ed="#Bc" n="46"/>quia primo de peccato originali in 
fo<lb break="no" ed="#Bc" n="47"/>mite, ibi, F, <quote xml:id="alalal-d99301-Qd1e208"> Quod autem quaedam 
pec<lb break="no" ed="#Bc" n="48"/>cata pena sunt, etc. </quote> Secundo in 
qui<lb break="no" ed="#Bc" n="49"/>busdam actibus qui diffiniuntur per 
pe<lb break="no" ed="#Bc" n="50"/>nam, sicut ira, invidia, et hujusmodi,
<lb ed="#Bc" n="51"/>ibi, G, <quote xml:id="alalal-d99301-Qd1e220"> Preterea nullatenus 
ambigen<lb break="no" ed="#Bc" n="52"/>dum, etc. </quote>
            </p>
